The final result is that $\int_{\Omega \times \Omega} \left(\sum_{i \in A} ‖X' i ω‖ ^ 2\right) ^ m \, d\mu(\omega) \cdot d\mu(\text{snd } \omega) \leq \int_{\Omega} \left(\sum_{i \in A} ‖X i ω‖ ^ 2\right) ^ m \, d\mu(\omega)$, which is precisely the inequality we need.
