$$\| \sum_{i \in A} X_i \|^2 \leq C \cdot \left( \sum_{i \in A} \|X_i\|^2 \right)^m$$

where $C$ is the Marcinkiewicz-Zygmund constant.

Looking at the proof goal, we need to show:

$$\int \|\sum_{i \in A} X_i \omega\|^{2m} d\mu \leq \text{marcinkiewiczZygmundConst}(2m) \cdot \int \left(\sum_{i \in A} \|X_i \omega\|^2\right)^m d\mu$$

