```

Now we need to show that $\text{marcinkiewiczZygmundSymmConst}(2m) \cdot \int \left(\sum_i \|\|X_i \omega\|^2\right)^m d\mu \leq \text{marcinkiewiczZygmundConst}(2m) \cdot \int \left(\sum_i \|\|X_i \omega\|^2\right)^m d\mu$.

$\text{marcinkiewiczZygmundSymmConst}(2m) = \frac{2m}{2}^{\frac{2m}{2}} = m^m$

$\text{marcinkiewiczZygmundConst}(2m) = 2^{2m} \cdot \text{marcinkiewiczZygmundSymmConst}(2m) = 2^{2m} \cdot m^m$

So we need to show $m^m \cdot \int \left(\sum_i \|\|X_i \omega\|^2\right)^m d\mu \leq 2^{2m} \cdot m^m \cdot \int \left(\sum_i \|\|X_i \omega\|^2\right)^m d\mu$.

